{
    "name": "Ankhrav",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ankhrav",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Ankhrav Burrows",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "As if the appearance of a hungry ankhrav in a stretch of farmland isn't bad enough, it almost always indicates the proximity of an ankhrav hive nearby. A disturbing number of ankhravs can infest a lair. However, adventurers brave enough to crawl through the tangled burrows are often rewarded with large amounts of treasure, as ankhravs have a habit of dragging their victims back to the deepest corners of their den to feast, usually discarding the remains with most of the gear intact.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core pg. 20",
                                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 20",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            },
                            "page": 20,
                            "errata": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "1.1",
                                "alt": "1.1",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Locations",
                        "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "text": "These horse-sized, burrowing monsters generally avoid heavily settled areas like cities, but ankhravs' predilection for livestock and humanoid flesh ensures that the creatures do not remain in the deep wilderness for long. Desperate farmers whose fields become infested by ankhravs often have little recourse but to seek the aid of adventurers.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Monster Core",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Monster Core pg. 20",
                        "alt": "Monster Core pg. 20",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 221
                    },
                    "page": 20,
                    "errata": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "1.1",
                        "alt": "1.1",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 221
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Ankhrav",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Ankhravs are immense, burrowing, insectile predators, considered by inhabitants of the rural areas of the world to be an all-too-common plague.",
